Galina Kopernak https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Galina_Kopernak 0 Galina Kopernak (March 22, 1902 – July 11, 1985) was a Russian theater actress who appeared on Broadway in the 1920s. She may have been originally from Shanghai. She came to the United States from Moscow.
